Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.80,0:00:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,晚上好欢迎收看TheCulpeperMinute \NGood evening, and welcome to The Culpeper Minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.60,0:00:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,自史上最畅销的自传——《面罩之下》 It's been nearly a decade.. .
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.20,0:00:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,披露最初的蒙面英雄团体 …since thebest-sellingautobiography Under the Hood.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.00,0:00:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“新民兵”的秘密以来 revealed secrets of the original band of masked adventurers.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.79,0:00:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,已有将近十年了 ..the new Minutemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.79,0:00:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,1975年TheCulpeperMinute刚在电视上播出时 In 1975, when TheCulpeper Minute was new to the airwaves..
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.20,0:00:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我们采访了《面罩之下》的作者———霍利斯·梅森 names ofw ons hande dig.Justwh Hehas attril …we profiled the author of Under the Hood, Hollis Mason.…. gone?you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.40,0:00:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,前任蒙面英雄人称夜枭 sofW ons h ustwh Hehas theformeradventurerknownasNiteOwl you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.20,0:00:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,在我最初的报道在1975年播出时《基恩法案》尚未通过 Whenmyoriginal report aired in1975,the Keene Act had notyetbeenpassed
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.20,0:00:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,现在这项有争议的法案禁止所有变装英雄和蒙面英雄的存在 Now,this controversial bill outlawed all costumed adventurers andmaskedheroes
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.80,0:00:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,考虑到目前围绕着蒙面正义这一主题的不安定局面 tigatior Given our current climate of unrest around the subject of masked justice..
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.20,0:00:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,考虑到目前围绕着蒙面正义这一主题的不安定局面 Given our current climate of unrest around the subject of masked justice..
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.80,0:01:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我们认为重温当初的故事 …we thought it would be interesting to revisit that original episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.80,0:01:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,提醒大家整个变装英雄事迹的开端 …as a reminder of where the whole phenomena….
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.40,0:01:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,会十分有趣 …of costumed heroics began.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.20,0:01:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,今晚我们将与霍利斯·梅森谈论他的自传——《面罩之下》 Tonight we're talking with Hollis Mason about his autobiography, Under the Hood.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.00,0:01:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,霍利斯·梅森的回忆录揭露了一些 Hollis Mason's memoirs revealed some of the secrets..
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.00,0:01:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,关于蒙面英雄的秘密 …of the maskedadventurers.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.60,0:01:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我与霍利斯在他最喜欢的纽约饭店theGungaDiner见了面 I met with Hollis at one of his favorite New York establishments,the Gunga Diner.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.79,0:01:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,在12岁时来到纽约 Coming to New York at 12 years old..
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.00,0:01:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,对我来说 在很多方面都很梦幻 it was, uh, fantastic for me in a lot of ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.80,0:01:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我的父亲在7号大街的弗农汽修店找到了一份工作 And my dad got a job at Vernon's Auto Repair off 7th Avenue.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.00,0:01:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,现在是梅森汽修店了 对吧？ Now Mason's,right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.20,0:01:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,没错 Now Mason's. Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.80,0:01:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,同一个地方 Same place.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.00,0:01:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,然而你没有追随你父亲的脚步 CULPEPER: Yet you didn't follow in your father's footsteps.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.80,0:01:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,你选择了另一条道路 Youchose another path
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.20,0:01:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,是的当我23岁时 MASON:Well,yeah,when Iwas2..
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.20,0:01:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我加入了纽约市警察局 ..IjoinedtheNew YorkCityPoliceDepartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.60,0:02:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我认为这跟我爷爷 And I think that that had a lot to do withmy grandfather..
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.40,0:02:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,以及他灌输给我的价值观有很大的关系 …andthevaluesthat he'd instilled inme
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.80,0:02:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,因为在12岁以前 很多时间是和我爷爷一起度过的 Because for thefirst 12yearsof my life,I spent a lotof time withmy granddad.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.40,0:02:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,他总是给我留下这样的印象 He was always keen to impress upon me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.19,0:02:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,乡下人在生活方式上比城市居民更道德 …that countryfolkweremorallyhealthier thancityfolk,thewaythey lived
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.19,0:02:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,当然 在某些方面乡下人会存在竞争 Of course you were competitive in certain ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.40,0:02:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,但他们也会互相帮助 But you were also-- You helped each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.00,0:02:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,这是一种刻在我脑子里的道德观 And it was kind of a moral value that stuck with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.20,0:02:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,当我第一次来到这座城市 And when I first got to the city..
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.80,0:02:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,看到的一些事情真的令我作呕 …there were thingsI sawthat reallyfilledmewithdisgust..
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.59,0:02:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,有些事我很难接受 that I found a hard time shaking, and, you know, some really--
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.80,0:02:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,有些到现在还是接受不了  Some of it I still can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.20,0:02:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我爷爷教给我的东西 What my grandfather gave me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.00,0:03:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,和我在这座城市面对的东西 …and what I was confronted with in the city-
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.40,0:03:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,当它们差距太大我实在接受不了时 When the distance between those things got too great and I couldn't deal with it..
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.40,0:03:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我就会投入别的世界———流行小说的世界 then I would go to myreal other world,the world of pulp-fiction novels.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.00,0:03:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,它们描述了一个有着绝对价值观的世界 They described a world of absolute values..
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.80,0:03:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,CATION 那个世界的真善美从不受怀疑 where what was goodand true was never in doubt
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.80,0:03:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,而邪恶 And evil was
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.80,0:03:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,总会受到应有的惩罚 An evririwas
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.80,0:03:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,总会受到应有的惩罚 Well, it received its appropriate punishment
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.60,0:03:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是你追求的生活吗？ Is thathowyou'veledyour life, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.00,0:03:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我一直在努力实现的 That's what I've tried to do. Um.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.80,0:03:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,没错 Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.20,0:03:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,霍利斯·梅森 理想化的年轻警察 Hollis Mason, idealizing young cop.….
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.80,0:03:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,试图理解他爷爷的乡村价值观 ….trying tomake sense ofgranddad's country values..
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.80,0:03:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,以及他自己居住的大城市的粗犷 …and thegritofthebigcityhefindshimself living in.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.00,0:03:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,很快警察及其代表的司法正义就无法满足年轻的梅森了 Soon enough, the police force and its brand of justice is not enough for young Mason.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.80,0:03:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,长期以来作为侦探小说和英雄主义漫画的粉丝 Long a fan of pulp detective fiction and comic-book heroics..
