Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.60,0:14:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我们中有些人是为了出名 有些人是为了权力 Some of us were in it for fame. Some for power.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.60,0:14:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,有些是为了躲避世界上的其他人 Some to possibly hide from the rest of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.60,0:14:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,但最终 我们的政治目的对我们想在那里做的事情 But in the end ofthe day,our politicsreallydidn't get inthe waytoomuch..
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.60,0:14:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,并没有太多的阻碍这是好事 …of what we wanted to be there to do, which was good
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.60,0:14:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我们在各自的社区里做了很多好事结果却一败涂地 We did too much good in our respective communities just to be written off.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.60,0:14:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我们都试图通过自己的努力 Wewereall attemptingthroughourpersonalefforts..
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.40,0:14:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,使我们的国家成为一个更好、更安全的居住地 …to make our country a better and a safer place to live
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.20,0:15:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,很明显霍利斯·梅森是一个从不为自己的生活 Clearly, Hollis Mason is a man who makes no apologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.40,0:15:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,和所做的决定道歉的人 …for the life he's livedor thedecisions he's made
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.20,0:15:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,但他的个人道德准则 But is his own personal moral code enough justification.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.80,0:15:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,是否足以成为他戴上面具、主持治安的正当理由？ for donning a mask and dispensing vigilante justice?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.20,0:15:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我走出去四处打听以便更好地了解 I went out and asked around to get a better sense
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.00,0:15:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,你们这些普通人对蒙面英雄的看法 …of how you, the people, felt about masked heroes
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.20,0:15:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道 MAN 1: I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.80,0:15:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我有很多顾客都是警察 I get a lot of customers that are cops.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.80,0:15:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,那些从我这里买了一包烟的家伙 Guys that comeby and pay for a pack of smokes from me everyday.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.40,0:15:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,他们告诉我这些蒙面英雄 …and they tell me that these masked adventurers..
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.40,0:15:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,他们让工作变得更困难了 ….they'remaking the job more difficult
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.60,0:15:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得他们怎么样？ MAN 2:What do Ithink of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.20,0:15:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以告诉你他们几乎毁了我的生意 They've just aboutdestroyedmybusiness, I can tell youthat.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.80,0:15:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,他们伤害了我的顾客 They maim my customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.80,0:15:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,他们喜欢折断手指 他们认为这很有趣 They like to break fingers. They think it's funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.80,0:15:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,没错他们很危险 Yeah. They're dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.60,0:15:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,但另一方面如果我们没有 But then on the other hand, what if we hadn't had..
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.80,0:15:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,曼哈顿博士那样的人站在我们这边呢？ …that Dr. Manhattan guy on our side, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.60,0:16:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我是说我知道这对我们来说是不可思议的 I mean, I know it's inconceivable tous, now knowing what we know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.60,0:16:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,但谁能说没有他们 ….but who's to say that things wouldn't have gone the same in Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.00,0:16:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,越南的情况就不会一样呢？ ...without them?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.40,0:16:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,如果在这场战争中战败 Losing that war.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.40,0:16:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,那会毁了我们的国家 That would've destroyed our country.
