Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.60,0:19:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,然后来出现了像大块头这样的现代超级反派 Minister ericans are making money fot the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.79,0:19:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,了像大块头 见代超级反 Despite al good trade ze countries,the call home. MInister Dess for the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.00,0:19:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,后来出现了像大块头这样的现代超级反派
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.00,0:19:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,那个身材矮小的犯罪大师正在市监狱服无期徒刑 …the diminutive master criminal now serving a life sentence in the city jail.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.40,0:19:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,你认为我是威胁 You think I'm the menace.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.00,0:19:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我不是戴着面具的人我没什么好隐瞒的 I'm not theone wearing amask. I got nothing to hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.00,0:19:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,那种戴着面具的是什么样的人？ What kind of person is that? Wear a mask?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.00,0:19:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我是个受人尊敬的商人 l'm a respectablebusinessman.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.20,0:19:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,找到神秘主义者摩洛克并不容易 CULPEPER: It wasn't easy finding Moloch the Mystic
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.79,0:19:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,不过话说回来 也不是太难 But thenagain,well, it wasn't too dificult.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.40,0:20:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,摩洛克就像战后许多声名狼藉的人物一样 You see, Moloch, like so many infamous figures of our postwar past.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.79,0:20:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,他们仅仅是进入了平民生活 ….had simply gone into civilian life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.00,0:20:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我那时比较年轻 MOLOcH: I was a younger man then.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.79,0:20:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我很叛逆 I was rebellious.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.00,0:20:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,就像你在附近看到的这些帮派一样 Knot Tops黑帮 Like these gangs you see around, the Knot Tops.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.20,0:20:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,当你生活在一个有着超人类权威人物的世界里 When you live in a world with superhuman authority figures.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.60,0:20:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你想反抗你必须进行更大规模的反抗 …and you wanna rebel, you have to rebel on a larger scale
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.79,0:20:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,你得把事件升级 You have to escalate things, you see
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.60,0:20:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,所以 So...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.60,0:20:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你成长在一个有超级英雄的世界里你想要反抗 …if you grow up in a world with superheroes and you wanna rebel..
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.20,0:20:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,你必须成为一个超级反派 …you have to become a supervillain.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.79,0:20:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,所以没错我认为没有超级英雄的社会会更好 So, yeah, I think society is better off without the superheroes..
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.20,0:20:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,因为这也意味着不需要超级反派 .because that means there's no need for any supervillains either.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.00,0:20:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢 MASON: Thank you. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.40,0:20:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,这种狂热持续了不到10年 You know, it didn't last, oh, 10 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.40,0:21:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,当50年代到来的时候人们对变装英雄的看法 When the '50s came, the whole perception of costumed adventurers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.40,0:21:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,完全改变了 你知道吗？ …you know, changed, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.40,0:21:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,那只是一时流行的狂热 It was a fad,yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.00,0:21:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,这种狂热正在消失而我们也在随之消亡 And the fad was dying out and we were dying with i.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.20,0:21:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,莎莉 Sally.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.00,0:21:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,她怀孕后就离开了 …well, shegot pregnant and she left.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.60,0:21:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我们其余的人被迫 The rest of us, we were forced to testify.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.00,0:21:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,在众议院非美活动委员会面前作证 .before the House Un-American Activities Committee.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.60,0:21:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,这是一场政治迫害 It was a witch hunt.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.60,0:21:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我们都被迫向其中一位众议院议员 We were all forced to reveal our identities..
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.00,0:21:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,透露自己的身份 to one of its representatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.40,0:21:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我是民兵组织的大都会队长 I am CaptainMetropolis fromtheMinutemen
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.40,0:21:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,幸运的是大都会队长有着杰出的军事履历 MASON: Now, luckily, with Captain Metropolis having such an outstanding military record.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.00,0:21:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,以及我在警察部门的工作 .and with my own service in the police force..
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.20,0:21:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我们都或多或少很快就消除了怀疑 …we both were more or less cleared of suspicion right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.80,0:21:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,蛾人遇到了更多的困难 Mothman met with more difficulty..
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.80,0:21:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,主要是因为他在学生时代结交的左翼朋友们 …mostly because of the left-wing friends that he'd cultivated during his student days.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.20,0:21:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,现在他终于被澄清了 Now,he's eventually cleared.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.20,0:22:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,但是调查过程漫长残酷 ….but the investigations,they were so lengthy and so ruthless…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.80,0:22:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我认为他因此承受的压力 ….that I think that the pressure he was under.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.20,0:22:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,加剧了他的酗酒问题 …it exacerbated his drinking problem…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.00,0:22:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,最终导致他精神崩溃 .anditcausedhiseventualmental breakdown
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.40,0:22:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,兜帽判官 HoodedJustice
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.80,0:22:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,拒绝作证 .refused to testify.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.20,0:22:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,因为他不准备向任何人透露他的真实身份 on the grounds that he was not prepared to reveal his true identity to anybody
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.40,0:22:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,当他们向他施压时 And when they pressed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.40,0:22:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,他消失了 .he disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.60,0:22:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我对他的这一行为充满了敬意 And Ireallyrespect himfor that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.60,0:22:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,他是我成为夜枭的原因 Hewasthereason IbecametheNiteOwl.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.40,0:22:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,直到今天我都不知道面罩后的那个人是谁 and I don't know to thisday who he was behind that mask
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.40,0:22:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,直到今大我都不知道面罩后的那个人是道
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.20,0:22:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,盲到今大我都不知道面罩后的那个人是道 anli don't know to thslay who he was behind tha
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.40,0:22:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,很有趣 不是吗？  Isn't that something?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.40,0:22:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我明白你想离开民兵组织是因为你怀孕了 Iunderstand that you wanted to leave the Minutemen because you got pregnant
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.80,0:22:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,但这是唯一的原因吗？ But is thatthe onlyreason?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.80,0:22:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,你从民兵组织退休还有其他原因吗？ Was there any other reasons that you retired from the Minutemen?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.60,0:22:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,有时候是时候往前看了 JUPITER: You know, sometimes it's just time to move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.80,0:23:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我没有怀孕的话 我想我会呆得更久 I think I would've stayed longer,had I not gotten pregnant
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.60,0:23:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,/ou tlose littlesignsofwhento take th
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.60,0:23:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,was
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.00,0:23:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,信号 itwas givesyouthpselitti
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.20,0:23:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,的信号 Ltitwas
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.40,0:23:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,t.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.00,0:23:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是其中一个原因 You know, and that seemed to be the one
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.20,0:23:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,在霍利斯的传记中 他声称你被笑匠性侵了 In his biography, Hollis alleged thatyou were sexually assaulted by The Comedian.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.00,0:23:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,但你从来没提过这件事 Yet you've never said anything about this
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.60,0:23:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么我现在要打破一生的习惯呢？ Well,whyshould I break a lifetime'shabitnow,right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.80,0:23:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,你作为一个记者问这个问题我不会指责你 I can't blame you for asking as a reporter.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.20,0:23:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,但是无可奉告 but, yes, it's-- No comment
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.40,0:23:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,莎莉·朱庇特和笑匠之间的那件事 Howmuch did the incident between Sally Jupiterand TheComedian…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.60,0:23:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,对你决定挂起面罩有多大影响？ …affect your decision to hang up the mask?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.00,0:23:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,有很大的关系 没错 Well, that had lot to do with it, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.60,0:23:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我认为一旦你意识到你的一些队友 I think once you realize that some of your teammates..
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.60,0:23:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,和你要追捕的罪犯一样堕落扭曲 …are just as depraved and twisted as the criminals you're going after..
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.40,0:23:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,没错 Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.60,0:24:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,这和我退出有很大关系 That had a lot to do with why I quit
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.40,0:24:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,那就是个谣言 There's no truthtothatrumor
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.80,0:24:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,如果发生了像这样的事 If something like that had happened..
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.40,0:24:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,你不认为我会建议莎莉提出刑事指控吗？ ….don't you think I would have advised Sally to have pressed criminal charges?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.40,0:24:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,她是我最好的客户我最大的收入来源 She was my best client. My biggest earner.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.60,0:24:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我绝不会让那样的事情逍遥法外 I wouldnever allowsomethinglikethattogounpunished
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.80,0:24:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,这不过是哗众取宠、 自我推销罢了 It's nothing more than sensationalism, self-promotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.00,0:24:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,霍利斯·梅森想卖出更多的书 HollisMason wantstosellmorebooks.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.80,0:24:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,笑匠拒绝谈论此事 CULPEPER:TheComedian declined tocomment.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.40,0:24:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,在我把雪茄塞进你眼睛之前把那东西从我脸上拿开 Get that thing out ofmy face before I put my cigar out in youreye.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.40,0:24:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,《面罩之下》是一本很棒的书 Under the Hood is a fantastic book
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.00,0:24:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,他是我的一个顾客 You know, he's one of my customers, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.40,0:24:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我经常见到他 I see him all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.80,0:24:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,关于超级英雄的这个问题很有趣这是一个非常微妙的界限 It's funny about this superhero thing, youknow, it's a very fine line
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.80,0:24:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,当你遇到像夜枭这样在你心目中是超级英雄的人 And when you got somebody like the Nite Owl who is your quintessential superhero
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.20,0:24:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,因为外面的这个家伙 because outside you get this guy
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.00,0:24:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,他变装后做各种各样爆炸之类的事 …who dresses up and does all the kaboom-kabang stuff
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.60,0:24:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,但他内心是个警察 member of the ...but inside he's a cop.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.80,0:24:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,所以他知道什么是忠诚守信你明白我的意思吗？ DWL  So he's a guy who knows what's true blue. You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.40,0:25:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,所以他知道什么是忠诚守信你明白我的意思吗? So he'sa guy who knowswhat's trueblue.Youknowwhat I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.00,0:25:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,他不喜欢这些附庸风雅的东西 He's not into these kind of artsy-fartsy things
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.40,0:25:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,他是个了不起的人 He's a great man.
