Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.00,0:32:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我想在这里说点私人的话题 So Iwant to get a littlepersonalhereforthemoment
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.60,0:32:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,你从没结过婚 这是为什么? You nevermarried.Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.80,0:32:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,呃 Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.40,0:32:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢 Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.00,0:32:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我想如果有什么原因导致我没有结婚的话 Well, I suppose if there's any one reason why I never got married..
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.80,0:32:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,是因为 …it was because.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.60,0:32:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,莎莉·朱庇特和别人结婚了 well, Sally Jupiter was taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.60,0:32:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我不认为我对她有感觉是什么天大的秘密 I don't think it's any great secret that I had a thing for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.00,0:32:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我不认为我对他有感觉是什么天大的秘密
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.80,0:32:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,有一半的男人喜欢她 Half the male population did.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.00,0:33:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,等我鼓足勇气约她出去的时候 Bythe time l'd rustled up the courage to ask herout on a proper date….
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.40,0:33:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,她已经和她的经纪人结婚了 …she was already married to her manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.60,0:33:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,每当我想到这件事的时候都会觉得很有趣 It's kind of funny when you think of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.40,0:33:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我打扮成猫头鹰 每天冒着生命危险 I dress up as an owl and risk my life on a daily basis.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.20,0:33:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,但说到约女孩出去 …but when itcame toasking a girl out…
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.20,0:33:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,这超出了我的能力范围 ..it was more than I could manage.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.00,0:33:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,可悲的是我认为我们的婚姻从一开始就注定要失败 Sadly, I think our marriage was doomed from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.40,0:33:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我在莎莉生活中的职业地位使我很难成为一个好丈夫 My professional position in Sally's life made it very difficult to be a good husband
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.00,0:33:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,作为她的经纪人 It was my job as her manager..
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.00,0:33:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我的工作不仅要接受男人被她吸引这一事实 …to not only accept the fact that men were attracted to her….
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.60,0:33:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,而且还要依赖这种吸引力 ..but to build on that attraction...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.00,0:33:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,来赚取利益 ..to prey upon it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.00,0:33:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,霍利斯对你来说非常重要 Hollis was very important to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.80,0:33:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,他是你生命中非常重要的人对吗? He was a very important person in your life, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.00,0:33:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,绝对的 Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.00,0:33:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,你们如今还保持联系吗？ You stay in contact with each other today?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.60,0:33:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,没错我们还在联系 We do. We do.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.40,0:33:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我得说没有我想要的那么多  Not as much as I would like, I must say.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.00,0:34:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,你的生活把你引向不同的方向 Youknow,your life takes youindifferentdirections..
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.20,0:34:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,但那确实是一段奇妙的时光 ..but that was really a magical, magical time..
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.80,0:34:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,当我们聚在一起的时候我们喜欢谈论过去的时光 .andwedoliketotalk abouttheoldtimes whenwegettogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.00,0:34:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我认为我还有一些 You know, I think--I think I still have some kind of.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.80,0:34:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,夜枭和丝魂总有一天会在一起 ..half-baked idea that...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.40,0:34:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,这种不成熟的想法 .Nite Owl and, uh. Silk Spectre are gonna end up together one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.80,0:34:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,当我们最初与霍利斯·梅森交谈时 When we originally spoke with Hollis Mason..
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.20,0:34:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,他相信他作为夜枭 ….he believed that the legacy he'd begun as the Nite Owl.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.80,0:34:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,以及和蒙面英雄团体的其他成员一起留下的遗产 …along with other members of the masked-hero community..
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.20,0:34:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,将会持续很多年 …would live on for years to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.40,0:34:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,他不知道自己错得有多离谱 He could not have known how wrong he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.20,0:34:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,这是当我们出于我们的道德观 This has been a nostalgic look back at a colorful time in this nation's past..
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.80,0:35:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,转向穿着卡通服装的华丽英雄时 …when we turned to flamboyant heroes with cartoonish outfits.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.20,0:35:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,对这个国家过去丰富多彩的时光的怀旧回顾 ..for our moral outlook.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.59,0:35:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,在后基恩法案时代我们现在生活在一个 In the post-Keene Act world we now live in.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.20,0:35:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,蒙面英雄已经过时且无关紧要的世界 ….the masked heroes are as outdated and irrelevant….
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.20,0:35:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,就像霍利斯·梅森在他的汽修店里修理的旧的破烂车一样 …as the old beat-up wrecks that Hollis Mason works on in his garage.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.00,0:35:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我们希望你会发现这次回顾的变装英雄的历史 We hope that you have found this look back at the history of costumed adventurers.….
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.20,0:35:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,既有启发性又有教育意义 ..both enlightening and informative.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.80,0:35:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我是拉里·卡尔佩珀这里是The Culpeper Minute I'm Larry Culpeper for The Culpeper Minute.
